(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Randallstown &mdash; Baltimore County police say an armed woman who barricaded herself and a child inside a suburban Baltimore apartment has been shot and killed by officers. Authorities say the child was shot in an extremity and taken to a hospital. The department said in a series of Tweets that detectives went to the apartment in Randallstown about 09:25 on Monday to serve an arrest warrant. Police say the woman named in the warrant was armed and had a child with her. It was not immediately clear the relationship between the woman and the child.Police say the detectives retreated and called for backup.The department Tweeted at 17:13 that the woman had been shot and killed and the child was taken to a hospital.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.